# 06 Rain, Server-Side APIs: Weather Dashboard

​

## Description

Weather Dashboard is a web application that allows users to quickly access weather forecasts for various cities around the world. Using OpenWeatherMap API, the application provides real-time weather data, including temperature, humidity, wind speed, and descriptions. Users can search for a specific city and view a 5-day forecast presented in user-friendly cards, each featuring icons representing weather conditions. Built with HTML, CSS (Bootstrap), and JavaScript, the Weather Dashboard offers a clean and responsive design, making it easy to stay updated on the latest weather information.
​

## Tasks

Search for City: Enter the name of a city in the input field and click the "Search" button to retrieve weather forecasts.

Display Forecast: The application fetches real-time weather data using the OpenWeatherMap API and displays a 5-day forecast for the selected city.

Forecast Cards: Each forecast is presented in a user-friendly card format, including temperature, humidity, wind speed, and weather descriptions.

Weather Icons: Weather conditions are visually represented with icons in the forecast cards, providing an overview of the expected conditions.

Responsive Design: The dashboard is designed using Bootstrap, ensuring a responsive layout that adapts to different screen sizes and devices.

Clean Interface: The interface is designed for ease of use, allowing users to quickly access and interpret weather information for their chosen cities.
​

